All Classes

  • Class Description
    App  
    Ball
    The Ball is a class that moves and destroys blocks.
    Block
    The Block class models a block that can be destroyed by Ball.
    BlockDestroyedMessage
    Message sent to signal when a block is destroyed
    Board
    The Board class aggregates block, ball, and paddle.
    BoardView
    Represents a view of the board.
    Breakout
    The main system/controller of this game.
    Constants
    Holds all of the constants for the game.
    EndGameMessage
    Message sent to signal the end of the game.
    Leaderboard
    Keeps track of all scores and orders scores from highest to lowest.
    LeaderboardMessage
    Message sent to signal score update.
    LeaderboardView
    This class shows the at most the top 10 scores.
    Life
    An object to keep track of lives.
    Message
    Message interface for all messages.
    MoveBallMessage
    Message sent to signal ball movement
    MovePaddleMessage
    Moves the paddle along the x-axis.
    Paddle
    Moves left and right using keyboard arrows.
    PlayAgainMessage
    Message sent to reset board to play again
    ResetMessage
    Message sent to reset the ball and paddle, and set the remaining life
    SaveScoreMessage
    Message sent to save the score.
    SaveScoreView
    Represents another view to save score.
    Score
    Keeps track of the user's score.
    Valve
    Acts as interface for other valves to handle messages.
    ValveResponse
    Indicates whether the Message was executed or not.
    View
    Serves as the main view for Breakout.
